        <font color="white" face="Verdana, Arial, Helvetica" size="2">You know, I am an american by birth. My grand father fought in the Korean war and in Vietnam. He earned the Medal of Honor in that war. He was the one that inspired me to join the Air Force. I spent several years in the USAF, and went to war twice during that time. I have faced death first hand, and escaped death myself by the grace of God. Who ever did this act of Satanism will be punished. In the ancient times, there was a practice; a sentence of death. It consisted of the person being straped to a large table, then slowly gutted. The person doing it, started with a deep slit in the abdomen. There were doctors of the time standing by to keep the guy alive for as long as possible. After this first slit was cut, they moved the cut straight up his stomach to just below the sternum. From here, the executor took his time rearranging the accused's intrails. This was a most agonizing death, with the person being revived from pain induced inconcousness several times during the hour or two procedure. When the person finally left this world, pieces of his body were sent to his friends and family to remind them of his doings. I beleive there is a perfect spot on top of the Statue of Liberty for this persons heart. The White House Lawn would be much more perfect with a head on a pole for all the would be terrorists to see. The President could request that every station in the world broadcast this live. Then maybe these hell spawn that did this(who ever they are be it other American, or foreign) will forever think twice before trying this again. Further more, if this was supported by another country, God save thier soul, for thier body and soil should soon be the worlds largest parking lot. What I would give to have 1 hour alone with the head person that did this(baseball bat, needle nose pliers, blow torch, vise grips, cigar cutter, a coat hanger, and a ball peen hammer, should be provided).</P><P>53 Hereti